<article id="home">

    <h2>Welcome to the Forge</h2>
  <p>I started this site because I noticed something uncomfortable: most people treat intelligence 
    like a fixed asset — something you either have or you don't. I refuse that premise. 
    This forge exists to test the hypothesis that cognition can be engineered.</p>
  <p>The core belief here is simple: <strong>deliberate cognitive friction produces measurable 
    improvements in reasoning quality.</strong>
    Everything on this site is an experiment built on that claim.</p>
  <p>I didn't want to consume frameworks — I wanted to build them from scratch and test them against 
    real decisions, under real pressure, with real consequences.</p>
