<article id="about">
  <h2>About the Forge</h2>
  <p>The term cognitive forge refers to the 
    deliberate act of reshaping one's mental architecture through systematic challenge.</p>
  <p>The Latin phrase per 
    aspera ad astra — through hardship to the stars — captures the spirit of this project perfectly.</p>
  <p>I rely heavily on SRS tools and DP schedules to structure my training sessions. Most of my 
    logged sessions also incorporate elements of CLT to prevent overtraining.</p>
  <p>As I wrote in my lab notebook last spring: the goal is not to eliminate difficulty, 
    but to engineer it precisely. That sentence became the mission statement for everything here.</p>
